version_description: THIS SONG IS NOT HARD TO PLAY. Look at my chords, they are somewhat special but sound very good and are not hard to play. (All based on Demo version.).
Sounds best with power chords. Very simple song, listen and play along to get the strumming right: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i862ft6sORw.

song_name: I Was Made For Sunny Days

version_description: Sweet song with a lullaby feel. Listen and play along to pick up on the hammer-ons and pull-offs used with the Dadd4 and the D/F# in the bridge: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JJd8Up-3zcQ.
There were a few issues in other tabs of this song but I didn't want to rewrite their work.
It's a song released by the weepies last year.
If you listen to the song, the strumming is very staccato for most of the song, especially the chorus.
A simple way to play the song.
Yep, Capo 10. Pretty high up there. See the guitar on the left in this live performance: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=djby_9Uji9k.
Includes fingerpicking and includes corrected chords and song structure.
